  <discussion>Variety grandiflora is recognized by its relatively large, pink corollas and 8–12 phyllaries. The size of the plants varies and stems are often somewhat woody near the bases. This variety appears to intergrade with var. arizonica and var. dianthopsis (S. L. Welsh et al. 2003).</discussion>
